Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Parser extracts too many false positives

Solution: Enhance filtering in clean_indicators() method
Add more legitimate domains/IPs to exclusion lists
Refine regex patterns for better precision
Issue: No techniques extracted from report

Solution: Check technique_patterns dictionary
Verify report contains technique keywords
Add more pattern variations for better coverage
Issue: Navigator layer doesn't load

Solution: Validate JSON syntax using python3 -m json.tool
Ensure technique IDs match ATT&CK format (T####)
Check that all required fields are present
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated the complete CTI analysis workflow: parsing threat reports, extracting indicators, mapping to ATT&CK framework, and visualizing results. These skills enable security analysts to transform raw threat intelligence into actionable insights for defensive and offensive security operations.

Key takeaways:

Automated parsing saves time and improves consistency
ATT&CK mapping provides standardized threat understanding
Visualization aids in communicating findings to stakeholders
Structured intelligence supports red team planning and purple team exercises
